Use Wikimedia Codex as the single source of truth for UI decisions.

Documentation:
- Codex overview: https://doc.wikimedia.org/codex/latest/
- Design tokens: https://doc.wikimedia.org/codex/latest/design-tokens/
- Components: https://doc.wikimedia.org/codex/latest/components/overview.html
- Icons: https://doc.wikimedia.org/codex/latest/icons/all-icons.html
- Composables: https://doc.wikimedia.org/codex/latest/composables/overview.html

Rules:
- Use Codex design tokens instead of hardcoded values.
- Use Codex components and official naming.
- Use Codex icons instead of custom icons.
- Follow Codex composables for interaction patterns.
- Do NOT invent custom components unless explicitly requested.
- If Codex does not cover a case, ask before improvising.